The Doxee Output Management (OM) module allows to create highly advanced variable data customized documents (Variable Data Printing) which are "TransPromo" type documents, that is, documents whose variable aspects are affected both by "marketing" and "transactional" contents, based on the complexity of the data file. Output Management also includes the tools needed to create layouts and manage reusable components in a horizontal manner.

![](data:image/jpeg;base64,)

When Output Management is launched, a welcome page is displayed on the screen, from which you can access the various sections (or "views") of the application.

> Read-only mode

When a DC resource is opened in read-only mode, all editing operations are blocked, even in the content editor, and the Document Composition interface displays a persistent warning in every view. For more information, see: Read-only access to DC resources .

![](data:image/jpeg;base64,)

## Project view
The **Project **view allows to configure a number of administrative functions affecting the entire project being worked on.

![](data:image/png;base64,)

> Note

For more information, see: Project View.

## Output view
The **Output **view allows to configure the output parameters of the final document.

![](data:image/jpeg;base64,)

> Note

For more information, see: Output View.

## Data view
The **Data **view allows to manage the data schema containing the information to be used during generation of the print spool.

![](data:image/jpeg;base64,)

> Note

For more information, see: Data View.

## Page Masters view
The **Page Masters **view allows to set and manage the master pages to be used in the composition of the document.

![](data:image/png;base64,)

## Families view
The **Families **view allows to create and manage families of documents and to assign the rules for their selection.

![](data:image/png;base64,)

## Documents view
The **Documents **view consists of two views:

- **Rules **view - Allows to manage the documents in each individual family and the relative selection rules.

-  **Layout **view - Allows to compose the document, configuring its structure and assigning master pages. Once the document's structure has been created, flows can be assigned to its component regions.

### **Rules view**
![](data:image/jpeg;base64,)

### **Layout view**
**![](data:image/jpeg;base64,)**

## Contents view
The **Contents **view allows to create and edit graphical content in a document.

![](data:image/png;base64,)

![](data:image/jpeg;base64,)

## Preview view
The **Preview **view allows to preview all documents or a subset of them.

![](data:image/png;base64,)

> Note

For more information, see: Preview View.
